gov.usgs.anss.edge

Class MiniSeedLog

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.edge.MiniSeedLog

  • public final class MiniSeedLog
extends java.lang.Object
    Examine any MiniSeed and 1) create log files from LOG channels, 2) send last sample from any non-administrative status channels to SeisNetWatch (mass position, voltages...), 3) do nothing on real data from transducers. This is called by the IndexBlock write methods mostly.

    If a channel is 'LOG', it is also written to the RLISS via the OutputInfrastructures. They like their log channels on LISS!
